<br>
  Just wondering what all your thoughts are on the best way for a druid to make some cash.  At current I am a level 9 (almost 10)  and I have like a total of 8 plat.  and all the armor and weapons are like 100's of plat or K's of plat,  how do you guyes make that much cash??   Just wondering....<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
    Your Broke Druid Friend<br>
            Taippen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usamita.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Samita</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/01 3:37:39 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Unless you concentrate solely on money monsters</span><hr size=1> wisps - stones<br>
dervs - bronze<br>
etc....<br>
<br>
you can expect to be broke until about lvl 20 to 25 <br>
kindof hang even and gradually make money until about lvl 35<br>
and then you will start banking some reasonable plat and buying nice things till about lvl 45 to 50<br>
after that unless you buy everything under the sun you should have a fair stash available<br>
<br>
This is how it was 2 years ago when I was a young druid<br>
with the items I used to droll over being much cheeper now you will probably have either more money sooner - or better items sooner than one of us old timers <p>Samita Littlethorn - Preserver<br>
Officer in Dealers of Death<br>
Solusek Ro<br>
<br>
Lvl 51 Monk - Phryar Tukk<br>
Lvl 46 Bard - Samiba Craftsman<br>
Lvl 44 Warrior - Samito Anklebane<br>
Lvl 31 Wizard - Alnar Alluria<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubuzwat.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Buzwat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/8/01 6:03:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Plat</span><hr size=1> 8pp EIGHT plat and your lvl 9 wow your rich.  I never had any money till I was in my mid teens.  <br>
Okay so I'm being sarcastic I always made money by looting all the corpses laying around every cp counts.  Get a couple backpacks so you can carry more and sell what ever you can find.  Then just hunt and the money will come.  Buy leather and be thankful that your needs are few.  One good way I made money was getting CB belts.  I never sold them but turned them in for exp and a ton of armor.  You can sell or wear.  But most importantly just hunt and loot.<br>
<br>
Cheers<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulilwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LilWolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/8/01 8:21:22 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Money...Money... Money...</span><hr size=1> Don't worry about cash for items.  A good set of PW for armor and a few crap weapons (practice both 1hs and 1hb).  This is all.  You will spend 100% of cash on spells.  Level 9 is usually the hardest to actually get all your spells.  14 is a little easier (since you can make money on sow... so after sow is bought, your done).<br>
<br>
btw, I didnt' have all my 9th spells until 11th I think.  If you have some extra cash, consider going for a forged 1hs or 1hb... You might also consider questing for a magic 2hb (forgot the name, the one that you go to Q, kill the dwarf in the bar, then go to Butcher)<br>
<br>
Don't worry about it.  Wisdom gear at your level is 100% useless (you'll get about 2mana per point in wisdom.  So you might be able to get 1/2 a fizzle if you tweak yourself up to 200wisdom).  <br>
<br>
goodluck<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujtoast.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jtoast</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/8/01 9:40:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Money...Money... Money...</span><hr size=1> Your talking about the bloodforge hammer quest.  <br>
<br>
As to weapons....you should be able to buy a velium weapon pretty cheap (10p max) on most servers.<br>
<br>
<br>
Tarrwin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubremen7.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bremen7</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/8/01 1:25:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> money</span><hr size=1> Go to the WK and kill bandits for the sashes and load up on them. For each red sash you turn in to that dude in NQ he'll give you XP and a weapon or bronze armor. Each weapon/item will get you about 2-3pp from the vendors. You can make a lot of quick plat for your level. Chesgard Syndwyn is his name or something like that been a long, long time since those levels.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showMessage?topicID=25068.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showMessage?topicID=25049.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.emailToFriend?topicID=25061.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.threadControl?topicID=25061.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=25061.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=25061.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of 